This paper focuses on utilizing FCNN-based dense semantic predictions for image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses handling semantic inefficiency, which involves optimizing the use of semantic cues, a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a way to use contour cues to improve segmentation robustness, which is a topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM).
